WEBVTT

00:00.835 --> 00:03.352
In New York City's war on crime,

00:03.352 --> 00:08.392
the worst criminal offenders are pursued
by the detectives of the Major Case Squad.

00:08.392 --> 00:10.190
These are their stories.

00:12.155 --> 00:15.479
One eighty-five, 190, 195.

00:15.479 --> 00:18.818
Oops. I'll be right back with the rest.

00:19.975 --> 00:21.715
Runnin' out of time, Chops.

00:21.715 --> 00:25.896
Hey, if he's breathin', we'll find him.
Don't even think about it.

00:26.717 --> 00:31.324
Sorry. Am I a bad accountant or what?

00:32.833 --> 00:35.464
See you next week, girlfriend.

00:35.751 --> 00:37.447
You put up with that crap?

00:39.005 --> 00:41.120
It's not forever.

00:41.905 --> 00:44.506
He's been in that apartment for a week.
He's going stir-crazy.

00:44.506 --> 00:47.294
It'd be a nice gesture,
considering what he's doing for us.

00:47.294 --> 00:49.815
I just need him to sit still for another week.

00:49.815 --> 00:52.979
If we don't get thrown another continuance.

00:59.413 --> 01:01.124
Here she comes.

01:01.336 --> 01:03.116
We go with her?

01:04.331 --> 01:07.093
No. Go buy a cake.

01:11.747 --> 01:14.648
So the big mystery's over.
Here's the address.

01:14.648 --> 01:16.351
No stops on the way there or back.

01:16.351 --> 01:18.051
Take him in and out through the back entrance.

01:18.051 --> 01:20.769
Inside, stay close.

01:22.061 --> 01:23.727
Here.

01:24.119 --> 01:26.606
So, what do you think?

01:27.157 --> 01:29.717
I think she's gonna be 
very proud of you, Danny.

